{{refimprove|date=September 2018}}
The '''[[Gurdwara|Gurdwara Sahib]] of [[Santa Rosa, California|Santa Rosa]]''' (also commonly referred to as the '''Santa Rosa Gurdwara''', the '''Sikh Temple of Santa Rosa''', or the '''North Bay Sikh Foundation''') is a center of [[Sikh]] worship.

==History==
The temple was founded in 2002, and according to a 2012 ''[[Press Democrat]]'' article, has about 100 members. It is a converted modular home located off Todd Road, in a ranching area.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kovner, Guy|url=http://www.pressdemocrat.com/news/2303855-181/we-are-sad-but-not?gallery=2354931&artslide=0|title='We are sad but not angry'|publisher=[[Press Democrat]]|date=August 6, 2012}}</ref>

