r. Uma Ukpai|work=www.nationswatch.com|date=2012–2013|accessdate=March 21, 2017}}</ref> He is the founder and president of [[Uma Ukpai Evangelistic Association]] (UUEA),<ref name="ReferenceG"/><ref name="ReferenceL"/><ref name="ReferenceK1"/><ref name="ReferenceM1"/> a [[nondenominational Christianity|nondenominational]] gospel ministry based in [[Uyo]], [[Akwa Ibom State]], [[Nigeria]].<ref name="ReferenceD"/><ref name="ReferenceB">{{ cite web|url=http://www.believersportal.com/lost-two-kids-one-day-rev-dr-uma-ukpai/|title= I Lost My Two Kids In One Day – Rev. Dr. Uma Ukpai|publisher=Believers Portal|date=November 3, 2016|work=www.believersportal.com|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceO">{{ cite web|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2016/12/16/my-calling-is-building-bridges-among-different-denominations/|title=My Calling is Building Bridges among Different Denominations|publisher=This Day|work=www.thisdaylive.com|date=December 16, 2016|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceQ"/><ref name="ReferenceU"/><ref name="ReferenceE1"/><ref name="ReferenceH1">{{ cite web|url=http://www.aksgonline.com.ws033.alentus.com/articlePage.aspx?qrID=1300&ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_grdArticles0ChangePage=5|title= University of Uyo Pledges Collaboration with Reverend Uma Ukpai’s Scholarship Foundation|publisher= Akwa Ibom State Government Online|date = February 17, 2014|work=www.aksgonline.com.ws033.alentus.com|accessdate=March 20, 2017}}</ref>
==Pentecostalism== Uma Ukpai is a Trustee of the Penticostal Fellowship of Nigeria (PFN) established in 1986.<ref name="ReferenceR"/><ref name="ReferenceD"/><ref name="ReferenceF">{{ cite web|url=http://etheses.bham.ac.uk/910/1/Burgess04PhD.pdf|title= THE CIVIL WAR REVIVAL AND ITS PENTECOSTAL PROGENY A RELIGIOUS MOVEMENT AMONG THE IGBO PEOPLE OF EASTERN NIGERIA (1967-2002)|publisher=RICHARD HUGH BURGESS |date=June 2004|work=etheses.bham.ac.uk|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref>{{rp|412}}<ref name="ReferenceN1"/> He is a Grand Patron, and a member of the National Advisory Council, of Penticostal Fellowship of Nigeria, PFN.<ref name="ReferenceR"/><ref name="ReferenceD"/><ref name="ReferenceS">{{ cite web|url=http://www.pfnriversstate.org/nac_members|title=NATIONAL ADVISORY COUNCIL MEMBER |publisher=Penticostal Fellowship of Nigeria, Rivers State Chapter: NATIONAL ADVISORY COUNCIL MEMBER|work=www.pfnriversstate.org|accessdate=March 20, 2017}}</ref>{{rp|412}}<ref name="ReferenceP1"/>
==Early life== Born in Asaga, [[Ohafia]], [[Abia State]],<ref name="ReferenceT"/><ref name="ReferenceP"/> Uma Ukpai met Jesus Christ in 1958.<ref name="ReferenceO"/><ref name="ReferenceA21"/> He lost his father to death at the age of 10.<ref name="ReferenceG"/> Uma Ukpai describing how his early life challenges nearly impaired his career development remarked “I know what it means to lose a father and be a father from that age. I know what it is to save money to pay school fees. So, I have feelings for the poor. I learnt early enough to know that the stone satan throws at you can become a stepping stone.”<ref name="ReferenceG"/>
==Education and Qualification== He attended Uma Ukpai Memorial Primary School, Asaga, and Khana County Council School, Ogoni. Uma passed through All Saints Secondary School, [[Aba, Abia|Aba]], and Niger Delta Technical School, now Boys Technical College, Aba. Uma Ukpai graduated from the School of Journalism and Television, Frisham, Hermitage, [[United Kingdom]]; South Florida Christian College [[Miami]], [[Florida]], USA; Carolina Christian University and Burke Bible College, [[Kentucky]], USA. He holds a Certificate in Electrical Engineering Practice, a Diploma in Journalism, a Bachelor and Doctorate Degrees in Divinity.<ref name="ReferenceD"/><ref name="ReferenceT"/>
==Family== Uma is married to Philomena Uma Ukpai, a pastor. Their marriage produced 8 children and an adopted child. Uma Ukpai lost 2 of his children in a car accident on the same day.<ref name="ReferenceZ">{{ cite web|url=http://www.danieldigest.com/dr-uma-ukpai-my-trials-and-the-triumph-of-faith/|title=Dr. Uma Ukpai: "My Trials and the Triumph of Faith.|publisher=Daniel Digest|work=www.danieldigest.com|accessdate=March 20, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceA21"/><ref name="ReferenceL">{{ cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2009/12/i-lost-two-kids-in-one-day-while-saving-my-wife-%E2%80%93rev-uma-ukpai/|title=I lost two kids in one day while saving my wife Rev. Uma Ukpai|publisher=Sam Eyoboka|work=www.vanguardngr.com|date=December 11, 2009|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceR1">{{cite book|author=Tobe Momah|title=Fear No Evil-By Hating Evil!: The Fear of the Lord Is to Hate Evil (Proverbs 8:13)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S9V4yOQT81MC&pg=PA116&dq=dr+uma+ukpai|date=July 2013|publisher=WestBow Press|isbn=978-1-4497-9935-9|page=116}}</ref>{{rp|116}}
==Ministry== Uma Ukpai is called to build bridges between different denominations through his evangelistic, prophetic and crusade ministry.<ref name="ReferenceO"/><ref name="ReferenceJ1">{{ cite web|url=http://nigeriaworld.com/articles/2011/feb/090.html|title=THE NIGERIAN PASTOR: Uma Ukpai|publisher=Mankind Olawale Oyewumi|work=nigeriaworld.com|date=February 9, 2011|accessdate=March 20, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceA12"/><ref name="ReferenceO1">{{ cite web|url=http://www.westafricadirectory.com/Nigeria/Religious_Organisations/Ministries.html|title=Uma Ukpai Evangelistic Association: Christian Ministeries in Nigeria-West Africa Directory|publisher=West Africa Directory|work=www.westafricadirectory.com|date=2004|accessdate=March 21, 2017}}</ref> For more than 30 years, the ministry has run a medical outreach whilst doing the work of God.<ref name="ReferenceG1">{{ cite web|url=http://thenationonlineng.net/cant-stop-helping-poor/|title=‘I can’t stop helping the poor’|publisher=Sunday Oguntola|work=thenationonlineng.net|date=April 24, 2016|accessdate=March 20, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceH1"/> [[Uma Ukpai Evangelistic Association]], UUEA, is one of the financiers of Penticostal Fellowship of [[Nigeria]], (PFN).<ref name="ReferenceK1"/><ref name="ReferenceM1"/><ref name="ReferenceR">{{ cite web|url=http://www.pfn.org.ng/board-of-trustees/|title=Board of Trustees: FOUNDING FATHERS’ CHURCHES|publisher=Penticostal Fellowship of Nigeria|work=www.pfn.org.ng|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceN1">{{ cite web|url=http://pfn-apapaisolo.org/|title=THE FOUNDING FATHERS OF PENTECOSTAL FELLOWSHIP OF NIGERIA|publisher=Welcome to Pentecostal Fellowship of Nigeria - Apapa Isolo Zone|work=archive.li|date=September 15, 2008|accessdate=March 21, 2017|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20080915021059/http://pfn-apapaisolo.org/|archivedate=September 15, 2008|df=}}</ref>
===Crusades=== Uma Ukpai has held many city wide crusades all over Nigeria. At present he holds a yearly crusade, Greater [[Ohafia]] For Christ Crusade and [[Anioma]] One-million Man Crusade, 2016,<ref name="ReferenceM">{{ cite web|url=http://aniomacrusade.com/we-are-bringing-a-man-that-has-a-mission-to-break-curses-in-our-land-celestine-iwendi/|title= WE ARE BRINGING A MAN THAT HAS A MISSION TO BREAK CURSES IN OUR LAND –Celestine Iwendi |publisher=Celestine Iwendi|date = January 13, 2016|work=aniomacrusade.com|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref> Nsukka 2012,<ref name="ReferenceD1">{{ cite web|url=http://www.adonsk.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/20TH-ANNIVERSARY-BOOK.pdf|title= ANGLICAN DIOCESE OF NSUKKA AT 20 Growth, Relevance and Future|publisher=Anglican Diocese of Nsukka|date = 2014|work=www.adonsk.com|accessdate=March 20, 2017}}</ref>{{rp|73}} and Greater [[Ibadan]] for Christ 1982.<ref name="ReferenceL"/><<ref name="ReferenceM"/><ref name="ReferenceG"/><ref name="ReferenceD">{{ cite web|url=http://encomium.ng/victorious-army-ministries-perfect-plans-for-2014-bethel-victory-convention-2/|title= Victorious Army Ministries perfect plans for 2014 Bethel Victory Convention|publisher=Encomium|work=encomium.ng|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceQ"/><ref name="ReferenceV"/> It was his Greater [[Lagos]] for Christ Crusade of 1985 that gave birth to the Pentecostal Fellowship of Nigeria (PFN).<ref name="ReferenceN1"/><ref name="ReferenceK1">{{ cite web|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201602291169.html|title= Nigeria: PFN Relocates to Own Secretariat|publisher=Sam Eyoboka|date = February 27, 2016|work=allafrica.com|accessdate=March 21, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceM1">{{ cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2013/01/pfn-picks-oritsejafors-replacement/|title=PFN picks Oritsejafor’s replacement|publisher=Sam Eyoboka|date = January 20, 2013|work=www.vanguardngr.com|accessdate=March 21, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceD"/><ref name="ReferenceO"/> <ref name="ReferenceP1">{{ cite web|url=http://www.mf.no/sites/mf/files/users/Dokumenter/Forskning/Doktorgradsprover/2015/lendetheriseofpentecostalpower.pdf|title=The rise of Pentecostal power: Exploring the politics of Pentecostal growth in Nigeria and Guatemala|publisher=Gina Lende|work=www.mf.no|accessdate=March 21, 2017}}</ref>{{rp|99}}
===Medical Outreach=== Uma Ukpai is the chairman of Uma Ukpai Eye Centre, and King of Kings Hospital, a specialist hospital in [[Abia State]],<ref name="ReferenceB1">{{ cite web|url=http://news2.onlinenigeria.com/news/top-stories/151357-rev-uma-ukpai-i-was-duped-n3-5m-in-a-church.html#ixzz4bu9Dto35|title=Rev. Uma Ukpai: I was duped N3.5m in a church|work=news2.onlinenigeria.com|date=March 31, 2012|accessdate=March 20, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceC1">{{ cite web|url=http://www.chama.ca/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/REPORT-CHAMA%E2%80%99S-3RD-MISSION-TRIP-TO-AFRICA-2.pdf|title=CHAMA’S 3RD MISSION TRIP TO AFRICA. November 1ST –9TH 2010 –Medical Missions, Water Well Projects, Health, Hygiene and HIV/AIDS Education campaign, School Supplies, Spiritual/Biblical teachings|publisher = Challenge Aids and Malaria in Africa, (CHAMA)|work=www.chama.ca|accessdate=March 20, 2017}}</ref> that services communities in [[Abia State|Abia]], [[Akwa Ibom State|Akwa Ibom]] and [[Cross River State]]s.<ref name="ReferenceG">{{ cite web|url=http://thenationonlineng.net/uma-ukpai-evangelistic-association-inc-showcasing-gods-love-boundless-possibilities/|title= UMA UKPAI EVANGELISTIC ASSOCIATION INC Showcasing God’s love and boundless possibilities|publisher=Sunday Oguntola|date = April 24, 2016|work=thenationonlineng.net|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceB"/><ref name="ReferenceD"/>
===Academic Institutions=== He is the proprietor of Uma Ukpai School of Theology and Biblical Studies, [[Uyo]],<ref name="ReferenceZ1">{{ cite web|url=http://www.newsexpressngr.com/news/detail.php?news=12479&title=Gov.-Udom-promises-steady-water-supply-for-Akwa-Ibomites-within-first-100-days|title=Gov. Udom promises steady water supply for Akwa Ibomites within first 100 days|publisher=Kalu|date = June 28, 2015|work=ohafia-tv.com|accessdate=March 21, 2017}}</ref> Uma Ukpai Polytechnic Asaga, Uma Ukpai Scholarship Foundation and Joseph business school, affiliate of Joseph business school Chicago, USA.<ref name="ReferenceH1"/><ref name="ReferenceG"/><ref name="ReferenceN">{{ cite web|url=http://newsexpressngr.com/news/detail.php?news=12200&title=Rev.-Uma-Ukpai-demands-prayers,-respect-for-Nigeria%E2%80%99s-leaders|title= Rev. Uma Ukpai demands prayers, respect for Nigeria’s leaders|publisher=Effiong Udousoroh|date = June 17, 2015|work=newsexpressngr.com|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceO"/><ref name="ReferenceP">{{ cite web|url=http://ohafia-tv.com/?p=424|title=OHAFIA MONARCHS PAY A COURTESY VISIT TO REV. DR. UMA UKPAI ON BEHALF OF DR. OLUGU UKPAI|publisher=Kalu|date = August 16, 2016|work=ohafia-tv.com|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceQ">{{ cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=APT8DQAAQBAJ&pg=PT89&lpg=PT89&dq=uma+ukpai&source=bl&ots=mb-wdSuMHq&sig=6PVJ-WFBbYJPsm9Wz6tzp7hogzc&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiFx6Cy3ePSAhVbF8AKHZYxCFY4UBDoAQgcMAE#v=onepage&q=uma%20ukpai&f=false |title=How the Spirit Shapes Prayer: Research Findings for Traditional Christians|publisher=David S. Luecke|date = January 19, 2017|accessdate=March 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceU"/>
